A couple days ago Pablo departed from us… I don’t usually post about this kind of stuff… or even at all but I remember how much of a fixture he was and how much I shared him with you guys.. Pablo had a great life, sadly one day the vet spotted something on his ear which turned out to be a Mast Cell Tumour. I was advised to remove it which meant surgically removing his ear also.. he made a slow and steady recovery back to his loveable self but unfortunately after about 6 months the tumour came back and continued to spread throughout body to the point where the vet deemed he no longer had a good quality of life. I never thought a dog would come with such personality or energy but Pablo was truly like no other and he will be missed.

I’ve not been on here much of recent.. but life is very much life-ing. So much has happened, changed and this rollercoaster never stops.. so I decided to make a visual scrapbook to fill you guys in. Full video on my official YouTube if you can be bothered.
